title: How To Make Cold Ramen
description:
Subscribe to Munchies here: http://bit.ly/Subscribe-to-MUNCHIES

Got hunger pangs? Richie Nakano of San Francisco hotspot Hapa Ramen shows us how to make cold ramen with his fridge leftovers (in his case: kimchi, chili peppers, corn, pea shoots, baby chard, scallions, furikake, and a poached egg) and a soy-ginger vinaigrette that will fill your belly with deliciousness in no time.
